## TL;DR — Yellow Gold Oval Diamond Engagement Ring in {{year}}

A yellow gold oval diamond engagement ring is the single most popular engagement ring style in {{year}} — it has been for three consecutive years. The combination is not a trend. It is now the dominant format for oval diamond buyers: the warm gold band enhances the oval's organic curves, the yellow tone eliminates the need to buy expensive white-looking color grades, and the aesthetic reads as vintage-adjacent without being costume jewelry.

**The most-reviewed yellow gold oval ring on Blue Nile:** [Classic Six-Prong in 14K Yellow Gold at $1,000](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/classic-six-prong-solitaire-engagement-ring-in-14k-yellow-gold-item-203272?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — 1,894 reviews.

**The critical strategy:** A G or H color oval diamond set in 14K yellow gold reads as colorless on the finger. The same stone in platinum reads as faintly warm. Choosing yellow gold allows buyers to drop one color grade and save $1,500–$3,000 on a 2ct oval without any visible difference in appearance.

**The sweet spot build:** [Classic Six-Prong at $1,000](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/classic-six-prong-solitaire-engagement-ring-in-14k-yellow-gold-item-203272?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) + [2ct GIA G-VS2 oval at $17,480](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?Shape=Oval&Carats=2&Color=G&Clarity=VS2&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) = **[$18,480 total](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?MetalType=yg&ShapeID=Oval&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**.

