## Halo Settings in Yellow Gold for Oval Diamonds

A halo setting adds a ring of accent diamonds around the center stone, increasing apparent face-up size by 20–30%. In yellow gold, the warm tone of the band carries through the halo frame — creating a cohesive warm aesthetic that white gold halos do not deliver. The halo's accent diamonds sparkle against the gold background differently than they do against white metal.

Yellow gold halos work particularly well with G or H color center stones — the warmth throughout the ring reads as intentional design rather than a color mismatch. This is another expression of the Gold Warmth Arbitrage.

